    List&lt;?&gt; newList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(oldList);
    for (int i : indicesToRemove) {
      newList.set(i, null);
    }
    newList.removeIf(Objects::isNull);

This way does not require sorting the indexes to be removed and takes advantage of the fact that `ArrayList` has its own optimal `removeIf` implementation.

