If the entry exits you add a new map with the description. If it doesn&#39;t you create a new map and add it. 

You can even leverage `Map.computeIfAbsent(k, func)` to have it in one expression:

(If you really want it in one line)

    definitions.forEach( d -&gt; map.computeIfAbsent( d.name(), k -&gt; new HashMap&lt;String,Definition&gt;()).put(d.desc(), d));

